B.aC4=new A.AV("Posterior Cord (C5-T1)","Axillary nerve + Radial nerve + Thoracodorsal + Subscapular nerves","Deltoid, teres minor (axillary); triceps, brachioradialis, all wrist/finger extensors (radial); latissimus dorsi (thoracodorsal)","Posterior cutaneous nerve of arm, lateral cutaneous nerve of forearm (via radial), regimental badge area (axillary)","If deltoid AND triceps/wrist extensors are weak, but biceps and hand intrinsics are normal, think Posterior Cord.","Absent radial SNAP with normal LABC and ulnar SNAPs = posterior cord",B.mM,B.mD,B.rI,null)
B.aC5=new A.AV("Medial Cord (C8-T1)","Ulnar nerve + Medial root of Median nerve + Medial pectoral nerve","All ulnar-innervated hand intrinsics (FDI, ADM, interossei); APB, opponens pollicis (medial median contribution); FDP to ring/little (ulnar)","Medial antebrachial cutaneous (MABC) -- medial forearm; ulnar nerve -- small finger and medial hand","If ALL hand intrinsics are weak (both ulnar and median-innervated) but deltoid and biceps are normal, think Medial Cord or Lower Trunk.","Abnormal MABC SNAP is the key localizer -- it branches directly from the medial cord, not from the ulnar nerve.",B.ae,B.ci,B.eK,null)
B.aC6=new A.AV("Lateral Cord (C5-C7)","Musculocutaneous nerve + Lateral root of Median nerve","Biceps, brachialis, coracobrachialis (musculocutaneous); pronator teres, FCR (lateral median contribution)","Lateral antebrachial cutaneous nerve (LABC) -- lateral forearm","If biceps AND pronator teres are weak, but hand intrinsics and deltoid are normal, think Lateral Cord.","Abnormal LABC SNAP with normal ulnar SNAP = lateral cord (not lower trunk)",B.ar,B.d8,B.rO,null)
