c4=A.ci("Severe Carpal Tunnel Syndrome with Axonal Loss",c6,k0,"INDICATED (Severity Assessment)",A.a([A.u(!0,f0,f0,j8,f0,h3,g9,h0,f0,t6,h1,f0),A.u(!1,"Spared (Critical: confirms lesion is at the wrist)",f0,f0,f0,f0,w2,h0,f0,f0,o8,f0),A.u(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,h5,h6,f0,f0,h1,f0),A.u(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,h8,h9,f0,f0,i0,f0),A.u(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,w5,f0,f0,f0,f0,k6)],n),"Severe CTS characterized by chronic compression leading to axonal loss (thenar atrophy). NCS shows absent sensory responses and a very delayed/low-amplitude motor response. EMG confirms active and chronic denervation in the thenar muscles.",c5,"severects",c7,ae8,ae7,!0,c4,A.a(["Thenar atrophy is a clinical hallmark of SEVERE carpal tunnel syndrome with secondary axonal loss.","Absent Median SNAPs are common in severe cases; the diagnosis is confirmed by excluding more proximal lesions using needle EMG.","In severe CTS, the Median CMAP distal motor latency is typically >6.0 ms and the amplitude is reduced (<4.0 mV)."],af3),"Severe Hand Numbness with Visible Wasting")
ae7=A.ch(45,"Burning and numbness on the outer part of the right thigh.",i1,"Patient wears a heavy duty belt for 10-12 hours a day. Over the last 4 months, he has developed a 'fire-like' sensation on the lateral aspect of his right mid-thigh. It is worse with standing and better with sitting. No weakness in the leg. No back pain.",x5,"Police Officer","Obesity (BMI 33), Type 2 Diabetes")
ae8=A.cm("Normal muscle bulk in the lower extremities. No skin changes.","Tapping over the lateral aspect of the inguinal ligament (near ASIS) reproduces the burning sensation (Tinel's sign).",ad9,"Full ROM of the hip, knee, and ankle.","Decreased sensation to light touch and pinprick in a well-circumscribed oval area on the lateral thigh. Normal sensation in the groin and medial/anterior thigh.","Negative Reverse SLR (for femoral nerve tension). Negative SLR.","5/5 Strength throughout the right lower extremity (Iliopsoas, Quadriceps, Adductors, TA, EHL, Gastroc).")
c7=A.a([A.Y("Meralgia Paresthetica (LFCN)",d9),A.Y("L2 or L3 Radiculopathy","Radiculopathy would typically cause weakness in the hip flexors or quadriceps and potentially a decreased patellar reflex. This patient has 5/5 strength and normal reflexes."),A.Y(x7,"Would cause weakness in the quadriceps and numbness on the anterior/medial thigh (not lateral thigh)."),A.Y(ae0,"Causes lateral hip pain and tenderness over the greater trochanter, but not cutaneous numbness or burning in the LFCN territory.")],ae9)
c5=A.a9(["constitutional","Negative.","musculoskeletal","Lateral thigh discomfort.","neurological","Pure sensory burning on the outer thigh."],af1,af1)
